<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA VOICES / A FORUM FOR COMMUNITY ISSUES: LETTERS TO VOICES ; 
'A REFRESHING CHANGE' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I thoroughly enjoyed Ted Lepon's article ("They Come to Gaze, to Wander, to 
Shop," May 30). I found this article to be a wonderful, refreshing change from 
the sensationalized news depicting the violence of gang drive-by shootings, 
carjackings and other crimes of escalating proportions that so often appears in 
the media. 
</P>
<P>
 Perhaps if we would all make it a point to focus our minds and attention on 
the many good things going on in the city -- instead of the bad -- this may be 
the start of getting back our once-beloved City of Angels as well as our 
sanity.  
</P>
<P>
 Harriet K. Bilford 
</P>
<P>
 Northridge 
</P>
</TEXT>
