<HEADLINE>
<P>
O.C. PLATFORM; A JOB FOR PARENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reacting to recent support from the mayor and public schools superintendent 
in Santa Ana for plans to help the city's youth, and to one mother's remark 
(after her son was arrested) that no one at school had let us know that he was 
headed for trouble, KATHY BROWN of San Juan Capistrano told The Times: 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 His parents should know him far better than any schoolteacher, counselor or 
administrator.Why then assign the primary responsibility for his upbringing to 
the school? 
</P>
<P>
 As a mother of five, I am appalled by the lack of commitment and direct 
involvement on the part of today's parents in the raising of their children. 
</P>
<P>
 This deficiency of dedicated parents who are committed to raising their 
children as decent citizens with respect for themselves and for the rights and 
property of others spans all economic levels. 
</P>
<P>
 We need more parents to communicate with their children. The responsibility is 
ours -- not some external agency. Our future lies in strong supportive 
families. 
</P>
</TEXT>
