<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOLF ROUNDUP; JANZEN ENDS SLUMP, GAINS CONFIDENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lee Janzen didn't look like a man worried about a jinx. 
</P>
<P>
 Not with a $216,000 check in his pocket for winning the Buick Classic on 
Sunday at Harrison, N.Y. Not with the millstone of a yearlong slump finally 
removed from his neck. 
</P>
<P>
 Janzen shot a 66 in the three-stroke victory over Ernie Els. 
</P>
<P>
 But it is true, someone told him, that no tournament winner has gone to the 
U.S. Open the next week and also won. 
</P>
<P>
 "Yet," he shot back. 
</P>
<P>
 The Janzen who emerged 51 weeks ago with a surprising victory in the 1993 U.S. 
Open, appears to be back. Just in time for the 1994 Open, which begins 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Dave Stockton salvaged a par out of a horrible drive on the 18th hole and beat 
Bob Murphy by one shot to win the Senior PGA Tour Nationwide Championship at 
Alpharetta, Ga. Stockton had a four-under 68 Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Liselotte Neumann had an eagle and five birdies in shooting a six-under 66 to 
win the Minnesota LPGA Classic at Brooklyn Park, Minn., by two strokes over 
defending champion Hiromi Kobayashi. 
</P>
