<HEADLINE>
<P>
LAKEWAY WINS MOTHER GOOSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Making amends for her loss to Sardula in the Kentucky Oaks, Lakeway rolled to 
a 4 1/4-length victory over 27-1 shot Cinnamon Sugar in the $200,000 Mother 
Goose Sunday at Belmont Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Winning for the fifth time in six races, Lakeway went head-and-head with 7-10 
favorite Inside Information for most of the 1 1/8 miles, put her away after 
some rapid splits (45 1/5 and 1:08 3/5) and won in a stakes-record 1:46 2/5 
under Kent Desormeaux.She paid $4.60 as the second choice. 
</P>
<P>
 "I told Kent to ride like it was a match race," said trainer Gary Jones. 
"That's what it looked like on paper. Don't let (Inside Information) get too 
far away." BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
