<HEADLINE>
<P>
BULLFROGS BEAT FLASH, STAY UNDEFEATED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Bullfrogs beat the Las Vegas Flash, 4-3, in a Roller Hockey International 
game Sunday at the Thomas & Mack Center in Las Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
 Anaheim, undefeated in two games, was ahead, 4-1, before Las Vegas scored 
twice in the second half but couldn't slip anymore past Bullfrog goaltender 
Chris Gordon, who made 26 saves. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bullfrogs led, 2-1, at halftime thanks to by Jim Brown and Brad McCaughey. 
Victor Gervais gave them a 3-1 lead 21 seconds into the third quarter. Steve 
Beadle scored with about four minutes left in the third quarter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA061394-0062 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 050930 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
