<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTLAKE'S HIRSH LEADS MARMONTE LEAGUE ALL-STARS TO VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL LAZARUS, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Before the Marmonte League faced the Channel League in the Ventura County 
All-Star baseball game Sunday at Moorpark College, the two teams engaged in a 
home run-hitting contest. 
</P>
<P>
 The results were indicative of the game that followed.No player was able to 
clear the fence in the contest -- and, in the game, neither team got an 
extra-base hit. But the Marmonte League scored four runs in the sixth inning 
and held on for a 5-2 victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Chuck Hirsh of Westlake had three hits, including a two-run single in the 
sixth that erased a 1-0 deficit. Kevin Sass of Agoura, who did not start, had 
two singles and was the only other player with more than one hit. 
</P>
<P>
 "Both teams went with their best pitchers early and that kept the hitting down 
for a while," Sass said. "Maybe I got a little lucky by coming in in the middle 
of the game." 
</P>
<P>
 The Channel League scored the first run in the fifth without a base hit. Sean 
Coker reached on a walk, advanced to second on a ground ball out, went to third 
on a wild pitch and scored on an error by Channel Islands shortstop Johnny 
Olivares. 
</P>
<P>
 Rene Sanchez of Channel Islands, the third pitcher for the Marmonte League, 
gave up one run and no hits in two innings to earn the win. 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley's Kary Kozlowski pitched two innings and earned the save. 
</P>
<P>
 Earlier, Moorpark's Jason Adamson had three hits as the Frontier League 
All-Stars routed seniors from the Tri-Valley League, 14-0. 
</P>
</TEXT>
