<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: HEALTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dow Corning Cites Bankruptcy Option: The company might consider filing for 
Bankruptcy Court protection should too many women opt out of a proposed 
$4-billion settlement of silicone breast-implant liability cases, a spokesman 
said.That scenario is unlikely, the spokesman said, because the Midland, Mich., 
company is in good financial health and most women involved in the class-action 
suits will accept the deal. Plaintiffs have until June 17 to accept the deal or 
decide to pursue their own cases. The settlement covers Dow Corning Corp. and 
other manufacturers of the implants, which were used by millions of women. 
</P>
</TEXT>
