<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACIFIC WATCH: JAPAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Government to Begin Releasing Data on Service Trade: The Finance Ministry will 
by late 1995 begin releasing data on the country's service trade as part of the 
current account figures included in official international balance of trade 
statistics, Japan's Jiji Press reported. Based on a formula the International 
Monetary Fund adopted last year, the new account figures will track trade in 
sectors such as construction, finance, insurance, transportation and travel. 
The ministry may also divide payments data into capital and current account 
balances, Jiji said. 
</P>
