PACIFIC WATCH: AUSTRALIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Unemployment Rate Falls to 9.8%: The figures for May, released last week, hit 
9.8%, the lowest level since August, 1991.The April rate was 10.1%. Employment 
rose a hefty 30,500 jobs, contrasted with a 5,800 increase in April. Analysts 
welcomed the data but warned that the central bank will have to raise interest 
rates if inflation is driven up by such strong employment growth. 
</P>
