<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOY, 15, HURT IN FALL AT DISNEYLAND HOTEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 15-year-old boy was injured early Sunday when he fell 20 feet from a 
Monorail platform at the Disneyland Hotel, the first serious accident since the 
ride opened in 1959, according to a Disneyland official. 
</P>
<P>
 The teen-ager, Edward Paolello of Santa Maria, was transported to UCI Medical 
Center in Orange immediately after the 12:30 a.m. fall.He was listed in fair 
condition with a shattered right elbow, a fractured left wrist and a hairline 
fracture of his pelvis, said Karen Wucetich, a hospital supervisor. 
</P>
<P>
 Paolello, who had been staying at the hotel with friends, was apparently 
accidentally pushed over a short wall and off the platform by a surge of 
Disneyland visitors as they left the Monorail, said his mother, Sylvia. 
</P>
<P>
 The teen-ager landed on a concrete parking area near the entrance to the 
hotel, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 "He had just gone through the turnstile and looked back to see his friend," 
said Sylvia Paolello, 42, a home health aide. "He didn't realize the change in 
the path and he wound up falling over the wall. He was so lucky, so lucky he 
wasn't more seriously hurt." 
</P>
</TEXT>
