<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD, SANTA PAULA; 4 MINORITY YOUTHS WIN 
SCHOLARSHIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY F. POLS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Channel Islands High School student who received a $3,500 scholarship from 
the Ventura County Minority Business Group will use the money to help pay for 
her first year at UC Berkeley. 
</P>
<P>
 But ultimately, senior Susana Pitones said, the investment made by the group 
will come back to the county when she returns with her college degree. 
</P>
<P>
 "I would like to come back to the county and work here," Pitones said. "I see 
a lot of need for Latinos to come back to Oxnard. I want to be a role model and 
show others that it can be done." 
</P>
<P>
 Pitones was one of four county high school students who each received $3,500 
scholarships from the group. Ventura County National Bank contributed $4,000 to 
the fund, and individual members of the group donated a total of more than 
$10,000. 
</P>
<P>
 The scholarship fund is in its second year. Winners are selected based on 
academic excellence, community involvement and financial need. 
</P>
<P>
 Other winners of $3,500 scholarships were Shelly Soto, a senior at Santa Paula 
Union High School; Juan Lechuga, a senior at Oxnard's Rio Mesa High School, and 
Christina Mata, also a senior at Rio Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition, 19 finalists each received $100 savings bonds from the bank. MARY 
F. POLS 
</P>
</TEXT>
