<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; BOLSA GRANDE TEEN TO JOIN SCHOOL BOARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Katrina Nguyen has been named student representative to the Garden Grove 
Unified School District Board of Education. 
</P>
<P>
 Nguyen, a junior at Bolsa Grande High School, will serve as a non-voting 
member with the board's five elected trustees for the 1994-95 school year, 
district spokesman Alan Trudell said. 
</P>
<P>
 Her other responsibilities will be to preside over monthly meetings of a 
student advisory committee to the board and serve as a liaison for the 
district's 41,000 students. 
</P>
<P>
 Nguyen, 17, said that she looks forward to representing the district and that 
the position is important in providing administrators and elected school 
officials a student's perspective. 
</P>
<P>
 Board members, who set policy, "don't go to school and don't always know what 
the students are facing. That's why it's so important to have a student on the 
board, to share with the older generation what it's like nowadays in school," 
she said. JON NALICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
