<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: IRVINE; SENIOR CARE CENTER PLANS JULY OPENING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city's Adult Day Health Center is scheduled to open next month alongside a 
new senior facility in Woodbridge village. 
</P>
<P>
 The center will provide frail and ill seniors with medically supervised care 
during the day, as well as other health services. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials plan to welcome the facility's first clients July 5. An open house 
for seniors and their families is scheduled for July 1 from 1 to 4 p.m. For 
enrollment information, call (714) 724-6950. 
</P>
<P>
 The health facility is next to the Irvine Senior Center, which opened in 
April. The senior center boasts meeting rooms, a library, auditorium, activity 
rooms and a large kitchen that will be used for a meals-on-wheels program. 
</P>
<P>
 The two facilities make up a 5,600-square-foot complex that officials hope 
will become a central location for senior services and events. 
</P>
<P>
 The senior center hosts a variety of activities such as exercise classes, 
health lectures and dances. 
</P>
<P>
 The day-care center is designed to assist seniors with a variety of health 
problems, including arthritis and Alzheimer's disease. The center will also 
provide care for people who have had strokes or other debilitating illnesses. 
</P>
<P>
 Clients will receive hot meals, nursing services and various forms of 
counseling. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials are developing a transportation system that will provide users with 
rides to and from the center. SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</TEXT>
