<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: IRVINE; CLASS TO HELP SENIORS ORGANIZE FINANCES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Irvine Valley College is sponsoring a course this summer to assist senior 
citizens with financial planning. 
</P>
<P>
 The class will be held at the new Irvine Senior Center and will be taught by 
Michael Trank, a certified public accountant who is active with the college's 
foundation. 
</P>
<P>
 Trank will discuss budgeting, cash flow, income taxes, inflation and long-term 
financial planning. 
</P>
<P>
 Special attention will be paid to health care issues, rising taxes and lower 
interest rates -- all of which can have a serious impact on the finances of 
retirees. 
</P>
<P>
 The course also will help seniors develop personal investment strategies and 
manage investments during retirement. 
</P>
<P>
 The class is free to seniors, but there is a $3 fee for materials. The class 
meets Tuesdays from 6 to 8:45 p.m. beginning June 28. It runs through Aug. 2. 
</P>
<P>
 The Irvine Senior Center is at 20 Lake in Woodbridge village. For more 
information, call (714) 559-3212. 
</P>
</TEXT>
