</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Officials searching for witnesses to a stabbing that occurred in Thousand Oaks 
last week are offering $1,000 for information that leads to an arrest. 
</P>
<P>
 A 21-year-old man was in the parking lot of a Thousand Oaks convenience store 
on Thousand Oaks Boulevard on June 3 when he was approached by a man who 
accused him of entering gang territory, according to a statement from Ventura 
County Crime Stoppers. 
</P>
<P>
 Another man then approached the 21-year-old, stabbed him, pushed him down and 
kicked him in the head several times, the statement said. 
</P>
<P>
 The two suspects retreated to a black Honda Accord that was driven by a woman, 
the statement said. The victim received several stitches and was released from 
the hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone with information about the incident is asked to call Ventura County 
Crime Stoppers at 494-TALK. 
</P>
<P>
 Callers will remain anonymous. MATTHEW MOSK 
