<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN IS JAILED AFTER ALLEGED GUN BATTLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man who fled after trading shots with an officer answering a 911 call at a 
residence here early Sunday surrendered later, authorities said. No one was 
injured in the exchange. 
</P>
<P>
 Howard Eakin, 25, whose hometown was not immediately known, was arrested on 
suspicion of attempted murder after fleeing from a residence about 2 a.m. at 
the 100 block of West Avenida Cordoba, said Orange County sheriff's Lt. Joseph 
Davis. 
</P>
<P>
 "When the first officer arrived," Davis said, "the suspect was in a front yard 
and started shooting at the deputy." 
</P>
<P>
 As the suspect repeatedly fired a handgun, Davis said, and the officer 
returned fire. However, neither the officer nor Eakin was hit, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputies had responded to a call from a woman who dialed 911 and said a man 
with a gun was at her residence. 
</P>
<P>
 After the brief gunfight, the suspect ran into the residence and fled through 
a rear door, Davis said. Eakin threw away the gun and hopped over a rear fence, 
prompting a "major search" of the neighborhood, Davis said. 
</P>
<P>
 Eakin later turned himself in, Davis said. 
</P>
<P>
 He was taken to Orange County Jail. 
</P>
